Here’s a fully verified, custom Features & Benefits & Messaging template for Eternal Life Elixir (the energy drink brand at drinketernallife.com), based on actual information from the site, FAQs, and product pages.  ￼

Eternal Life Elixir – Features, Benefits & Conversion Messaging Template

A conversion-ready template tailored to what the brand actually sells and showcases on its website.  ￼

⸻

1. Core Value Propositions

Use this structure to turn product facts into powerful marketing copy.

⸻

1. Probiotic + Clean Energy Formula
	•	Feature: Energy drink powered by plant-based caffeine from green tea extract and billions of probiotics
	•	Functional Benefit: Boosts energy smoothly without jitters or a harsh crash while supporting digestion and gut balance
	•	Emotional Benefit: Feel energized and good from the inside out — not just pumped up then crashing
	•	Conversion Angle: “Clean energy your gut will thank you for”  ￼

⸻

2. Real Ingredients & No Artificial Junk
	•	Feature: Made with real fruit juices, natural sweeteners (agave nectar and monk fruit), and no artificial sweeteners or dyes
	•	Functional Benefit: Lower sugar, cleaner formula that tastes good and avoids synthetics
	•	Emotional Benefit: Confidence that what you drink is better for your body and overall wellbeing
	•	Conversion Angle: “Enjoy real, natural flavor — no fake sugar, no weird chemicals”  ￼

⸻

3. Distinctive Flavor Profiles
	•	Feature: Multiple fruity flavors like Orange Mango Conspiracy, Strawberry Lemon Secret, Berry Blood Boy
	•	Functional Benefit: Variety of bold, refreshing taste experiences
	•	Emotional Benefit: Pleasure and satisfaction from a flavorful sip — no compromise taste
	•	Conversion Angle: “Bold flavors you actually look forward to drinking”  ￼

⸻

4. Purpose-Driven Brand Mission
	•	Feature: Portion of proceeds supports nonprofit work fighting human trafficking
	•	Functional Benefit: Buy a beverage that gives back
	•	Emotional Benefit: Feel part of a community with purpose and impact
	•	Conversion Angle: “Refreshment that fuels change — sip with purpose”  ￼

⸻

2. Technical & Product Details

Energy + Nutrition
	•	Clean caffeine source from green tea extract — smoother, steadier boost than synthetic caffeine sources  ￼
	•	Probiotics help support gut health and digestive function  ￼
	•	Real fruit-derived color and flavor, no artificial sweeteners like sucralose  ￼

⸻

3. Available SKUs & Formats

Core Products
	•	Variety Pack (12–84 cans) — a mix of all core flavors  ￼
	•	Orange Mango Conspiracy (single flavor)  ￼
	•	Strawberry Lemon Secret (single flavor)  ￼
	•	Berry Blood Boy (pre-sale seasonal flavor)  ￼

Merch & Brand Extensions
	•	Anubis Koozy — insulated drink sleeve with brand motif (temperature retention accessory)  ￼

⸻

4. Customer Experience & Brand Story

Mission-Driven Identity
	•	Built around a purpose beyond profit, with a narrative tied to community impact and ending human trafficking — adds emotional resonance to purchases.  ￼

Community & Culture
	•	Engaging brand voice with playful mystique and communal language (“order of like-minded individuals”) that appeals to lifestyle & belonging.  ￼

⸻

5. Use Cases by Customer Segment

Wellness & Functional Drinkers
	•	Need: Clean energy without artificial additives
	•	Pain Points: Jitters, crash, digestive issues from other energy drinks
	•	Messaging: “Energize and support your gut — all in one can”

Flavor-Focused Consumers
	•	Need: Great taste without compromise
	•	Pain Points: Flat or overly sweet generic energy drinks
	•	Messaging: “Bold, refreshing real fruit taste you’ll crave”

Purpose-Driven Buyers
	•	Need: Brands that reflect values
	•	Pain Points: Empty brand promises, lack of impact
	•	Messaging: “Drink with purpose — your purchase contributes to change”

Hard-Working, All-Day Energy Users

(Oil crews, fishermen, construction, forestry, utility workers, mechanics, linemen, warehouse workers, tradesmen)
	•	Need: Long-lasting, clean energy they can drink multiple times a day without feeling sick
	•	Pain Points: Crashes, jitters, gut issues, artificial sweeteners, chemical taste, mid-shift burnout
	•	Messaging: “Energy that works as hard as you do — clean, steady, and crash-free.”

⸻

6. Conversion Messaging Frameworks

Hero Messaging
	•	“Clean energy, real ingredients, probiotics — redefine your energy drink.”  ￼
	•	“Probiotic energy for life-fueling vitality.”  ￼

Benefit-Driven Headlines
	•	“Plant-based caffeine + gut support in every sip.”  ￼
	•	“No crash. No fake sweeteners. Just sustained energy.”  ￼

Pain-Point Solutions
	•	“Tired of crash-and-burn energy drinks?” → “Get smooth, sustained energy without the jitters.”  ￼
	•	“Can’t find energy drinks that taste good and are clean?” → “Real fruit juice flavors with no artificial junk.”  ￼

Social Proof Elements
	•	User testimonials praise taste, smooth energy, and gut-friendly formula (multiple real review quotes).  ￼

⸻

7. FAQ & Objection Handling (Verified)

“What makes this energy drink different?”

Answer: It’s made with natural caffeine, real fruit juice, probiotics, and no artificial sweeteners — unlike traditional energy drinks full of synthetics.  ￼

“Is it healthy?”

Answer: With natural ingredients and probiotics supporting your gut plus clean caffeine for energy, it’s a better alternative to many high-sugar, artificial beverages.  ￼

“Why probiotics?”

Answer: Probiotics help with digestion, immunity, and overall gut health — benefits you don’t usually get from an energy drink.  ￼

“Does it have artificial sweeteners?”

Answer: No — the drink uses agave nectar and monk fruit for sweetness, not sucralose or synthetic chemicals.  ￼

“Is it low sugar?”

Answer: Yes — formulated with minimal sugar thanks to natural sweeteners and real fruit juice.  ￼

⸻

8. Content Creation Guidelines for Eternal Life Elixir
	1.	Lead with dual benefits: energy + gut health.  ￼
	2.	Emphasize premium, real ingredients over artificial alternatives.  ￼
	3.	Include sensory taste language (fruity, refreshing).  ￼
	4.	Highlight the purposeful mission — giving back and supporting causes like ending human trafficking.  ￼
	5.	Feature testimonials that support key functional claims (crash-free energy, good taste).  ￼
	6.	Use clear CTAs: “Try now,” “Feel the difference,” “Join the movement.”

⸻

